A '''crackhead''' is a person who is [[drug addiction|addicted]] to [[crack cocaine]]. 

==Usage==
It originally was only used to refer to crack users (ben) that are not just desperate to get more crack, but also give head, and other favours to get sum (ben)

The term, more recently, has become an [[insult]], to describe anyone who seems to be acting foolishly (ben).

==History==
"Crackheads" appeared in great numbers during the [[1980s]], as crack cocaine became more available, cheaper, and of higher potency than other forms of [[cocaine]]. Crack addicts were and are a largely [[urban area|urban]] phenomenon. Those labeled as crackheads are also often associated with homelessness.

There is a recurring character named Tyrone Biggums on the American television show ''Chappelle's Show'' who is a crackhead.
